<Class name="BGP_Mutex" id="e1c1d6bf-c2aa-48c8-ae87-41a8e0d57956">
    <superclass name="BGP_Object"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>
********************************************************
********************************************************

NO longer used     Use CM_Mutex class instead.

********************************************************
********************************************************


This Class is used to single thread tasks.

Create an instance of this for each task that requires a mutex.
As the number of instances should be low we just foreach through BGP_Mutex.instances looking for
our instance. If this is to be used frequently (multiple calss per second) or the number of instances
grows to over 50, then a collection will need to be added.

A Global Constant Category MutexPrimaryValues exists with constants for each required task.
Mutex__Max holds the next available value. Increase this by 1 after creating a new constant. </text>
    <DbClassMap file="mutex"/>
